public class SmartServoLINOTGModule
extends com.kuka.roboticsAPI.controllerModel.sunrise.ServoInterpolator

This Module is used for linear smart servo motions.

This element is an undocumented internal feature. It is not intended to be used by applications as it might change or be removed in future versions.

computeTargetFrm

public double[] computeTargetFrm(com.kuka.roboticsAPI.geometricModel.AbstractFrame targetPose)
Compute the targetPoseFrame.
If a reference Frame is set the targetPoseFrm is referring to the reference frame. If no reference Frame is set, the targetPoseFrm is referring to the robRoot

Parameters:
targetPose - the new targetPose
Returns:
the new 3x4 Matrix - targetPose represented as row first double[].
